"35:40:1" : {s: 35, a: 40, w: 1, r: "قول", t: "قُلْ", l: "قَالَ", lc: 1618, tl: "qul", lb: "কথা বলা",e: "Say", b: "তুমি বল", i: "katakanlah", f: 218, rm: "to say/speak, to call, to be named, word/speech, utterance, a thing said, greeting, discourse, one who says/speaks. To inspire/transmit/relate/answer/think/profess, emit an opinion on, indicate a state or condition or circumstance. qailun - speaker, indicator.", ag: "فعل أمر ", eg: "Verb Imperative ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPV", qual: "", deg: "2", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "قَالَ،قَآئِلٌۭ،قَوْلٌۭ"},
"35:40:2" : {s: 35, a: 40, w: 2, r: "راي", t: "أَرَءَيْتُمْ", l: "رَءَا", lc: 271, tl: "ara-aytum", lb: "(ভেবে/চোখে/স্বপ্ন) দেখা, উপলব্ধি করা",e: "Have you seen", b: "তোমরা বল দেখি", i: "apakah kamu memperhatikan", f: 12, rm: "to see/think/hold, in opinion of, perceive, judge, consider, know. araitaka / araitakum - do tell me thou/you (the personal pronoun ك is added for emphasis and is not purely as pleonism without adding to the meaning). tarani is for a compound word of a verb tara followed by a pronoun ni - you see me. badi al-rayi - having superficial view, outward appearance, first thought, apparently, without proper consideration. rayalain - to see with naked eye, judgement by sight. riyun - outward appearance, make a show. ruya - vision dream. alam tara - behold! lo! riaun - hypocrisy, ostentation, to be seen. taraa - to see one another, consider, come in sight of one another. yurauna - they deceive hypocritically assuming a false appearance.", ag: "الف الاستفهام وفعل ماض وضمير متصل ", eg: "Interrogative alif and Verb Perfect and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "PERF", qual: "", deg: "2", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "رَءَا،رَأَىٰٓ"},
"35:40:3" : {s: 35, a: 40, w: 3, r: "شرك", t: "شُرَكَآءَكُمُ", l: "شَرِيك", lc: 40, tl: "shurakāakumu", lb: "অংশীদার",e: "your partners", b: "তোমাদের শরীকরা", i: "sekutu-sekutumu", f: 1, rm: "to be a companion, be sharer/partner. shirkun - share, participation, polytheism, idolatry, making associate/partner with Allah. shariik (pl. shurakaa) - associate, partner, sharer. Nouns of the second declension when followed by the affixed pronouns take the three inflexions thus shurakaa, shurakaai, shurakaaa. shaarak (vb. 3) - to share with. ashraka (vb. 4) - to make a sharer or associate, give companions (e.g. to God), be a polytheist or idolater. ashraktumuuni - you associated me as partner. mushrik - one who gives associate to God, polytheist. mushtarikun (vb. 8) - one who partakes or shares.", ag: "أسم منصوب وضمير متصل ", eg: "Noun Accusative case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACC", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَشْرَكَ،شُرَكَآءُ،شُرَكَٰٓؤُا۟،يُشْرِكُ"},
